<span id="freeTextContainer2110903227394918106">How to explain this book? It&apos;s basically a historical account of Van Gogh &apos;s life from a fictional perspective. Although Rachel did exist, nothing is known about her. This book really hit home for me as I too suffer from bipolar disorder. It was so easy to diagnose him after reading about his &quot;crise&quot;. So unfortunate that no therapy or even valid diagnosis was available in his lifetime. Makes me realize what my gate would have been had I been born during another era.</span>
  <span id="freeText2110903227394918106" style="display:none">How to explain this book? It's basically a historical account of Van Gogh 's life from a fictional perspective. Although Rachel did exist, nothing is known about her. This book really hit home for me as I too suffer from bipolar disorder. It was so easy to diagnose him after reading about his "crise". So unfortunate that no therapy or even valid diagnosis was available in his lifetime. Makes me realize what my gate would have been had I been born during another era.</span>
