              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=art-themed-fiction">art-themed-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=medical-fiction">medical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=epilepsy">epilepsy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=read-in-2009-11-november">read-in-2009-11-november</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=books-that-made-me-cry">books-that-made-me-cry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=best-of-2009">best-of-2009</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=around-the-world-in-80-books">around-the-world-in-80-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=best-5-star-nonseries-fiction">best-5-star-nonseries-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1313648-joseph?shelf=best">best</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79040723" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13916928741468956705">This was an amazing work of historical fiction. This author took bits and pieces of real history and wrote an incredible work of fiction. There are very few books that I have read that have touched me so that they have made me cry. This one did it throughout the telling of a very sad fictional love story involving Vincent Van Gogh in the last two years of his life.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


