<div id="review_1720806829" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1720806829" />
    <a title="Jan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16983722-jan"><img alt="Jan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1360066017p2/16983722.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1720806829?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jan" href="/user/show/16983722-jan">Jan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1720806829" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer983443597606166255">An engaging speculation of a love affair between Vincent Van Gogh and Rachel, a young lady of the evening, during the final two years of Van Gogh’s life when he lives in Provence. Enhanced by Rachel’s deep appreciation of Van Gogh’s many colorful paintings during this period, the story presents a very sympathetic portrait of the artist as he paints gloriously, loves deeply, and suffers immeasurably.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


